WEBVTT

00:58.892 --> 01:01.687
Hello? Is anybody there?

01:03.438 --> 01:05.732
Hey, honey, what's up?

01:05.816 --> 01:08.944
Slow down. Who are you talking about?

01:09.027 --> 01:12.447
No, I don't know! Sweetheart,
I don't have a clue what you're...

01:12.739 --> 01:14.241
An apartment?

01:16.827 --> 01:19.121
No, no! Of course I'm not
looking at an apartment!

01:19.204 --> 01:21.832
Why would I be
looking at an apartment?

01:23.458 --> 01:25.210
Wait a sec, wait. I know what this is.

01:25.294 --> 01:30.048
Oldest trick in the book. Yeah.
Did a realtor call you? Yeah.

01:30.090 --> 01:33.552
Yeah, realtor calls the wife, says,
"Oh, yeah, I spoke to the husband.

01:33.594 --> 01:35.721
"I'm looking at a..."

01:35.804 --> 01:38.932
My card? My business card?
I don't know.

01:41.351 --> 01:43.711
That I don't know. I don't know
why he has my business card.

01:43.729 --> 01:45.063
Maybe he...

01:46.398 --> 01:48.442
Maybe he or she, then.

01:50.611 --> 01:51.904
Yeah.

01:51.945 --> 01:54.239
Okay, surprise ruined.

01:54.323 --> 01:55.741
No, no, it's all right.

01:55.782 --> 01:57.784
It was gonna be for our anniversary,
but I...

01:57.868 --> 01:59.953
Yeah, it's just a little one-bedroom
in the West Village,

02:00.037 --> 02:01.288
but you're gonna love it.

02:01.371 --> 02:03.874
Yeah. Yeah, I know.

02:03.957 --> 02:06.293
Hey, listen, the car never picked me up
for this thing at the Waldorf.

02:06.376 --> 02:09.505
I got to go. I'll see you at home tonight,
okay, honey?

02:09.588 --> 02:12.049
I love you, too.

02:12.132 --> 02:14.510
It's okay. Big kiss.

02:14.593 --> 02:16.595
All right, then. Bye-bye.

02:24.978 --> 02:26.563
Hey, let me ask you a question.

02:26.647 --> 02:28.887
You a real estate broker
or a professional fucking idiot?

02:31.485 --> 02:33.946
Babe, I really think
we ought to let the super do that.

02:33.987 --> 02:35.781
No, I got it, I got it.
Just move that stuff.

02:35.822 --> 02:38.283
No, I did not say
my wife needs to see the apartment.

02:38.367 --> 02:41.828
I said Amber needs
to see the apartment. Amber.

02:41.870 --> 02:44.957
Amber sound like the wife
of a man my age to you?

02:45.749 --> 02:47.584
- Careful with my table!
- Yeah, picked it up right now.

02:47.668 --> 02:48.710
Okay, just get the cord for me, will you?

02:48.794 --> 02:50.963
Okay, all right. I got it, baby.
What do you want me to do with it?

02:51.004 --> 02:53.048
Just keep it out of my way.

02:53.674 --> 02:55.384
Well, it's not exactly a love nest

02:55.467 --> 02:58.011
if my wife's there picking out
the goddamned curtains, is it?

02:58.095 --> 03:00.055
Careful, just get the window,
get the window.

03:00.138 --> 03:01.515
- Okay?
- Ready?

03:01.598 --> 03:03.100
Yeah, just pull it down, and inside.

03:03.183 --> 03:06.311
No, I'm telling you right now,
stop talking.

03:06.353 --> 03:07.896
Because I'm thinking.

03:07.980 --> 03:11.984
No, I'm thinking! I don't...
You know what? Just kill it.

03:12.067 --> 03:14.319
No, kill it. Kill the whole thing.

03:14.403 --> 03:17.698
- There, good.
- See? DIY. "Do It Yourself."

03:17.781 --> 03:18.991
Oh, no!

03:22.995 --> 03:24.913
Call me over the weekend.
Leave a message on the home machine

03:24.997 --> 03:26.748
saying the seller's
had a change of heart,

03:26.832 --> 03:29.209
and that the whole thing's...

03:29.293 --> 03:31.336
- Oh, my God!
Dead.

03:37.259 --> 03:39.299
You are not gonna believe
what almost just happened!

03:42.723 --> 03:45.184
- Did you see that?
- Someone call 911!

03:46.059 --> 03:48.854
- Oh, my God, is he dead?
- He ain't happy.

04:02.117 --> 04:03.493
What?

04:08.290 --> 04:10.626
You cannot be serious!

04:14.963 --> 04:16.380
Not now.

05:32.666 --> 05:34.626
Okay, go ahead and spit.

05:37.880 --> 05:41.300
So, anyway, the very first scene
just takes your breath away.

05:41.341 --> 05:43.969
You have to remind yourself that
you're in the theater watching a play.

05:44.011 --> 05:47.347
My five-year-old, Alex, just adored it.

05:47.431 --> 05:50.142
He wanted his father to see it with us.

05:52.394 --> 05:54.021
That's better.

05:54.104 --> 05:57.691
Anyway, I think he really,
really enjoyed the costumes...

05:59.318 --> 06:01.570
Dr. Pincus? Hi.

06:01.653 --> 06:03.947
I'm gonna need
the panoramic X-ray machine

06:04.031 --> 06:05.199
for most of the morning tomorrow,

06:05.282 --> 06:07.659
so if that fits in
with your appointments...

06:07.701 --> 06:09.661
Fine.
I've cleared my schedule for tomorrow.

06:09.745 --> 06:10.954
Really?

06:13.624 --> 06:16.627
I hear it's supposed to be a lovely day.

06:19.505 --> 06:20.547
And?

06:21.465 --> 06:25.844
No, I just thought that maybe
you were taking the day off to go and...

06:29.056 --> 06:31.808
Right. Sorry to bother you.

06:34.061 --> 06:36.980
You know, we brought some cake.

06:37.397 --> 06:40.776
Mrs. Prashar and I
just had our baby, so...

06:43.737 --> 06:45.364
Yeah, it's a girl,

06:45.447 --> 06:52.162
and we're having a little cake
and I brought some pictures, so, if you...

06:52.246 --> 06:54.039
That'd be delightful.

06:56.083 --> 06:57.751
Start without me.

06:59.670 --> 07:02.881
Great, great. Okay, so...

07:08.595 --> 07:10.806
What a cute baby. She is so cute.

07:10.889 --> 07:13.058
- Yeah, she really is.
- How long was the labor?

07:13.100 --> 07:14.893
- Ten hours.
- Ten hours?

07:14.935 --> 07:16.186
- Yeah.
- Oh, my God.

07:16.270 --> 07:20.023
- That seems like a really long time.
- No, not really.

07:20.107 --> 07:21.817
- It's not?
- Not really.

07:21.900 --> 07:23.944
- See, that's, like, too long.
- It's so worth it.

07:24.027 --> 07:26.530
I'll just get a cat, you know?

07:26.613 --> 07:30.701
Like, 10 hours is a long time
to get something, you know?

07:30.784 --> 07:32.160
- Look at that.
- So cute.

07:42.546 --> 07:44.298
Stop global warming?

07:54.600 --> 07:57.561
Yeah, just a tiny...
It might take a little jiggle.

07:57.644 --> 07:59.438
Good evening, Doctor.

08:00.189 --> 08:02.733
You know what? Let me just open it.

08:04.610 --> 08:08.155
Hey! Can you hold the elevator?
Please?

08:08.238 --> 08:11.033
- Yeah. Holding.
- Thank you.

08:13.744 --> 08:17.414
- Sorry!
- Wait, hold. Hey! Hey!

09:29.486 --> 09:31.363
Good. Still some more.

09:44.626 --> 09:46.211
Come on, come on, come on,

09:46.295 --> 09:48.380
make it, make it, make it,
make it, make it, make it.

09:48.463 --> 09:51.842
<i>Paging Dr. Michael,
Dr. Michael to Pediatrics, please.</i>

09:51.925 --> 09:53.645
- Charts come back up, yet?
- They're there.

09:53.677 --> 09:54.720
I appreciate it.

09:54.803 --> 09:57.848
<b>- Spell it.
- P-I-N-C-U-S.</b>

09:57.931 --> 10:00.517
- Date of birth?
- Why?

10:00.601 --> 10:02.019
What day were you born?

10:02.102 --> 10:04.897
No, I understood the question.
Why do you need to know that?

10:04.938 --> 10:07.482
Let's leave it blank. Weight?

10:07.566 --> 10:09.443
- Last night or this morning?
- You pick.

10:09.526 --> 10:11.195
Hundred and eighty-two pounds.

10:11.236 --> 10:13.614
Number of alcoholic beverages
consumed per week?

10:13.697 --> 10:16.074
- Why do you need to know that?
- Well, they want to know.

10:16.116 --> 10:17.576
Well, I'm sure
"they" want to know a lot of things,

10:17.659 --> 10:19.369
but I don't want my intimate details

10:19.453 --> 10:21.622
auctioned off to the highest bidder,
willy-nilly.

10:21.705 --> 10:22.915
I'll put zero.

10:22.956 --> 10:24.958
- Marital status?
- Pass.

10:25.042 --> 10:26.960
- Profession?
- Irrelevant.

10:27.044 --> 10:30.297
- Food allergies?
- I'm not gonna be eating here.

10:30.380 --> 10:33.342
- Are you allergic to sticking plaster?
- What a ludicrous question.

10:33.425 --> 10:34.718
I'm not answering
any more of these, really.

10:34.801 --> 10:36.428
- Do you smoke?
- Stop it.

10:36.470 --> 10:38.514
- Do you wear dentures?
- Madame, listen.

10:38.597 --> 10:43.352
- When was the last time you ate?
- A pertinent question at last.

10:43.435 --> 10:45.312
Yesterday, lunchtime.
Thanks for asking.

10:45.395 --> 10:47.523
I had a tuna sandwich.
Toast was soggy, but...

10:47.606 --> 10:50.692
- Did you drink the laxative solution?
- Yes.

10:50.776 --> 10:52.152
Did it work?

10:53.111 --> 10:56.240
It was as advertised.

10:56.281 --> 10:58.450
Did you evacuate your bowels?

10:58.534 --> 11:01.578
I drank copious amounts
of drain-cleaning fluid.

11:01.662 --> 11:03.497
<i>What followed was fait accompli.</i>

11:03.580 --> 11:05.100
Sir, what I'm asking is if you were...

11:05.165 --> 11:10.337
I shat. Okay? Good. Again and again.

11:10.420 --> 11:13.924
It was like a terrorist attack down there
in the darkness and the chaos,

11:14.007 --> 11:15.843
the running and the screaming, okay?

11:15.926 --> 11:18.428
- Fine with me.
- Good.

11:18.512 --> 11:20.597
Gross invasion of my privacy, this.

11:20.681 --> 11:23.141
Wait till they get you in the back.

11:24.768 --> 11:26.854
- Good morning, Dr. Pincus.
- Hi.

11:26.937 --> 11:28.272
Don't anticipate any difficulties today.

11:28.313 --> 11:30.148
We'll have you up
and on your feet in no time.

11:30.232 --> 11:31.275
- Okay.
- Quick question.

11:31.316 --> 11:33.443
I notice you requested
a general anesthetic.

11:33.485 --> 11:35.988
It's not really typical
for this type of procedure.

11:36.071 --> 11:37.614
- It's not necessary and we normally...
- Sorry.

11:37.698 --> 11:40.492
I have no intention of being around
when they go where they're going.

11:40.576 --> 11:42.786
When does the surgeon arrive?

11:42.870 --> 11:44.079
I'm the surgeon.

11:44.163 --> 11:45.956
- Really?
- Yeah.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.583
- Why do you look that tan?
- Thanks for noticing.

11:47.666 --> 11:50.127
I got a spray tan
on my way to work today.

11:50.210 --> 11:53.005
- Looks natural.
- Yes. It's better for you.

11:53.088 --> 11:55.248
<b>It's moisturizing
and it doesn't cause UV damage, so...</b>

11:55.257 --> 11:56.341
Yeah.

11:56.466 --> 11:58.635
It has an odd smell.
I can't quite place it.

11:58.719 --> 12:01.513
- I don't know if...
- No, I don't want to smell your fake tan!

12:01.597 --> 12:03.265
- What are you...
- It's like dirt.

12:03.348 --> 12:06.685
But like a garden dirt, like a good dirt.
Not like a garbage dirt.

12:06.727 --> 12:09.521
- You gonna go darker?
- I think I am. I think I'd like to go darker.

12:09.563 --> 12:11.190
It's really gonna make my eyes pop.

12:11.273 --> 12:13.775
You could get your teeth whitened
like I did.

12:13.859 --> 12:14.985
- Yeah, that makes a difference.
- Very nice.

12:15.068 --> 12:18.197
Yeah, I don't like having trays
in my mouth and my teeth are small.

12:18.238 --> 12:19.573
Sorry, you babbling idiots.

12:19.656 --> 12:22.951
Can we talk about my bowels?
Wouldn't that be a good idea?

12:23.035 --> 12:25.316
Looks like the sodium thiopental's
really kicking in, huh?

12:25.329 --> 12:28.290
- Makes people say crazy things.
- I haven't given it to him yet.

12:28.373 --> 12:30.459
- Going in now.
- How old are you?

12:30.542 --> 12:33.253
So are you here on a school field trip?

12:33.921 --> 12:35.964
Not a real people person are you,
Dr. Pincus?

12:36.048 --> 12:39.718
Not really. Given a choice between
a few people and loads of people,

12:39.760 --> 12:42.054
I choose my cat. She hunts dwarves.

12:42.137 --> 12:44.056
She takes them up the tree.
They're still alive.

12:44.097 --> 12:45.557
You can see their little legs going.

12:45.641 --> 12:48.435
Sounds like Norah Jones
when she plays the piano.

12:56.151 --> 12:59.029
Wow, you must be excited
to get home and see your cat.

12:59.112 --> 13:00.155
What cat?

13:00.239 --> 13:02.074
I thought yesterday
you said you had a cat.

13:02.157 --> 13:06.745
I despise cats. What sort of men
waste their affection on a cat? Pathetic.

13:06.829 --> 13:09.248
I had a cat once, when I was a little girl.

13:09.373 --> 13:12.084
My father, right before he died,
he took me to the shelter and he said,

13:12.167 --> 13:13.460
"Debra, take a look
at all these lonely cats..."

13:13.544 --> 13:15.420
What a wonderful man
he must have been.

13:15.462 --> 13:16.547
Now, listen.

13:16.630 --> 13:18.190
All those people in my room last night,

13:18.215 --> 13:19.925
I thought I was dreaming at first,
but I wasn't.

13:19.967 --> 13:21.468
Who were they?

13:22.177 --> 13:24.429
- I don't know anything about that.
- Right.

13:24.513 --> 13:28.183
- Here you go. Clean bill of health.
- All right, thank you.

13:29.351 --> 13:31.395
Come back soon!

13:31.436 --> 13:34.356
What a terrible thing to say
in a hospital.

13:47.911 --> 13:49.079
Nice.

13:49.788 --> 13:52.749
Fine example for healthcare workers.

13:52.833 --> 13:56.003
Still, I suppose
smoking serves a purpose.

13:56.086 --> 13:59.590
- Thins the herd. Weeds out the stupid.
- Are you speaking to me?

13:59.631 --> 14:01.550
Yeah, but I was having a go at them,
not you.

14:01.633 --> 14:02.885
Oh, good.

14:02.968 --> 14:06.680
I picked one that should be
in a straightjacket. My mistake.

14:13.437 --> 14:17.065
Show it some attention,
it follows you home. Unbelievable.

14:19.193 --> 14:20.402
Sorry!

14:24.364 --> 14:26.116
Did he see you, too?

14:31.079 --> 14:32.414
- He can see us!
- Who?

14:32.498 --> 14:33.790
That guy?

14:40.047 --> 14:42.508
Hey, why don't you open your eyes?

14:50.974 --> 14:52.184
Hey!

14:53.227 --> 14:54.686
Hey, mister!

14:55.521 --> 14:57.356
Please, just hold up!

14:58.065 --> 15:00.067
- Idiot. Get out of the road.
- Wait! Hey!

15:00.150 --> 15:03.153
- Listen, I just need two minutes...
- Look out!

15:07.407 --> 15:09.034
Of your time!

15:10.077 --> 15:11.870
You can see me, huh?

15:13.831 --> 15:15.624
And you're not like us.

15:15.707 --> 15:18.794
I know you're not, because back there,
that cab almost hit you!

15:18.877 --> 15:21.713
And he honked at you,
and he yelled at you!

15:22.256 --> 15:24.925
I don't feel well. Why on earth...

15:26.260 --> 15:27.344
Hey!

15:35.894 --> 15:37.688
Officer, there's loony weirdoes.

15:37.729 --> 15:39.565
I don't know why they're here.
I'm a dentist.

15:39.606 --> 15:41.859
- Hey, man, you can see me.
- Oh, good.

15:41.900 --> 15:44.152
Hey, come back here!
I wanna talk to you!

15:44.236 --> 15:45.696
Hey, don't be scared! I'm a cop!

15:45.779 --> 15:47.948
- He can see us?
- Who? That guy?

16:19.688 --> 16:21.315
From the moment I left the hospital.

16:21.398 --> 16:24.151
- What kind of side effects?
- Hallucinations.

16:24.234 --> 16:25.944
- Okay, visual or aural?
- Both.

16:26.028 --> 16:31.450
And really vivid, really realistic, weird.
I mean, that's not normal.

16:31.491 --> 16:35.287
Well, you know.
What's normal, you know? Really.

16:37.164 --> 16:39.041
Not having hallucinations,
I'd have thought.

16:39.124 --> 16:42.419
Did anything unusual happen
during my procedure?

16:42.503 --> 16:44.129
- Did any...
- Did any what...

16:44.171 --> 16:46.840
- Sorry, but did anything...
- Where?

16:46.924 --> 16:49.301
- Why do you just keep talking while...
- I didn't hear what...

16:49.384 --> 16:52.513
- Why do you keep interrupting me?
- No, well...

16:52.596 --> 16:55.766
- Did anything unusual happen...
- You kind of interrupted me a little bit.

16:55.807 --> 16:57.434
- Just answer the...
- Just.

16:57.518 --> 16:59.269
- Did anything unusual happen?
- Where?

16:59.353 --> 17:02.898
What do you mean, where?
That's not a proper... Yes or no?

17:02.981 --> 17:04.861
Did anything unusual happen
during my procedure?

17:04.942 --> 17:05.943
- Yeah.
- What?

17:06.026 --> 17:08.069
- No.
- You said "yes" first.

17:08.153 --> 17:13.492
"No" is what I ended with.
"Yes, no" means no.

17:15.868 --> 17:18.288
Did anything unusual happen
during my procedure?

17:18.372 --> 17:21.208
- And if so...
- Can you hold on one...

17:21.290 --> 17:23.292
Can you hold on a second?

17:25.671 --> 17:27.130
Yeah, it's me.

17:27.798 --> 17:31.593
Can you stop what you're doing
and come down here right away?

17:33.387 --> 17:36.014
It's that thing that we talked about.

17:37.057 --> 17:40.561
Yeah, well, you told me to call you
if it came back, and it came back, so...

17:40.644 --> 17:42.020
Okay.

17:42.062 --> 17:44.690
What was that? What's the thing?
You told someone the thing came back.

17:44.773 --> 17:48.902
I have a rash on my back.
It came back, so I had to call my doctor.

17:50.445 --> 17:51.780
You... Miss!

17:51.864 --> 17:52.865
- Yes?
- Me!

17:52.948 --> 17:55.576
- What the... What?
- Can you...

17:55.701 --> 17:57.286
- Can I... Yes.
- Follow you?

17:57.369 --> 17:59.121
- To the...
- To my office.

17:59.204 --> 18:01.540
- And then you'll tell me.
- Yeah.

18:04.751 --> 18:05.878
What?

18:09.464 --> 18:11.717
Did anything unusual... What?

18:13.051 --> 18:16.013
Jesus Christ! Sorry, I wasn't...

18:16.221 --> 18:20.392
We have a meeting in a couple minutes,
so we just have to be quick.

18:22.603 --> 18:26.982
Did anything unusual happen
during my procedure? What's he...

18:27.065 --> 18:29.401
Can you please define "unusual"?

18:31.236 --> 18:34.114
Out of the ordinary,
bizarre, unanticipated.

18:38.076 --> 18:39.536
No, this went well.

18:39.620 --> 18:42.331
- It was good. Okay, normal.
- Right.

18:42.414 --> 18:44.583
Yes, good. Well, the cessation maybe,

18:44.666 --> 18:47.503
- but after that, you responded...
- The cessation of what?

18:47.586 --> 18:50.047
Dr. Pincus, I really...
I don't need to tell you that

18:50.130 --> 18:52.883
every medical procedure
doesn't follow the same path.

18:52.925 --> 18:53.967
- Everyone's different.
- Yeah.

18:54.051 --> 18:56.411
There are subtle variations
in even the simplest surgical...

18:56.470 --> 18:59.223
What would a subtle variation be
in my case, for example?

18:59.264 --> 19:02.267
- Well, one doesn't wish to use jargon.
- No.

19:02.351 --> 19:05.521
- But, you know, technically...
- Yep.

19:05.604 --> 19:07.898
Medically, it's beginning...

19:11.401 --> 19:13.153
Okay. Yeah.

19:13.237 --> 19:15.239
- You died.
- I died?

19:15.280 --> 19:17.449
- Little bit.
- For how long?

19:17.533 --> 19:19.451
- Seven minutes.
- A bit less.

19:19.493 --> 19:20.786
I died for seven minutes.

19:20.828 --> 19:21.870
- A bit less.
- Approximately seven...

19:21.954 --> 19:24.039
That's really the only thing
that I can think of...

19:24.122 --> 19:26.333
How did I die?

19:26.416 --> 19:30.087
For the record, we did not recommend
that you use the general anesthesia.

19:30.128 --> 19:33.966
When you use anesthesia,
there is a chance, although it is small,

19:34.049 --> 19:37.010
of a biochemical anomaly.

19:37.094 --> 19:39.888
Where's the anesthesiologist?
I want to see him now.

19:39.972 --> 19:41.390
He does not work here anymore.

19:41.473 --> 19:43.433
You'll be happy to know
that at Saint Victor's,

19:43.517 --> 19:46.395
we have a very strict
three-strikes policy.

19:48.021 --> 19:50.399
My anesthesiologist had two strikes?

19:50.482 --> 19:53.318
Okay, let's all calm down.

19:53.402 --> 19:57.030
Let's just not overdramatize
the situation.

19:57.114 --> 19:58.991
Why is he calming down?

20:00.993 --> 20:02.578
Everybody dies.

20:05.622 --> 20:09.126
Yeah, but usually at the end of their life,
and just the once and forever.

20:09.168 --> 20:10.836
Everybody's different.

20:10.919 --> 20:12.671
And you weren't even gonna tell me.

20:12.754 --> 20:14.673
